  "texts": [
    "Take T = d-dimensional pure Spin(2N) gauge theory.",
    "(32) This theory has (27) 0-form symmetry arising from the outer-automorphism of the gauge algebra so(2N).",
    "The non-trivial 2-representation is furnished byW S ⊕ W C, (33)where W S is Wilson line in irreducible spinor representation S of so(2N) and W C is Wilson line in irreducible cospinor representation C of so(2N).",
    "Indeed, the outer-automorphism exchanges the spinor and cospinor representations, and hence the two Wilson lines are exchangedW S ←→ W C,(34)under the action of ( 27).On the other hand, there are representations of so(2N) left invariant by the outerautomorphism, e.g.",
    "the vector representation V. The corresponding Wilson lines are left invariant by ( 27), e.g."
  ],
